    {
      "name": "Reports",
      "item": [],
      "description": "# API Automation Framework — Test Report\n\n## Overview\n\nThis report documents all API endpoints tested within the **API Automation Framework** collection. The collection is organized into two functional modules: **Auth** and **User Management**. All requests target the `{{baseUrl}}` environment variable.\n\n---\n\n## 1\\. Auth Module\n\n### POST `/user/login` — Login\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | POST |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/user/login` |\n| Auth | None (public endpoint) |\n| Content-Type | `application/json` |\n\n**Request Body:**\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"username\": \"kminchelle\",\n  \"password\": \"0lelplR\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Purpose:** Authenticates a user and returns an access token used for subsequent authorized requests.\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `200 OK` with a JWT token in the response body.\n\n---\n\n### POST `/auth/login` — Login Request\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | POST |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/auth/login` |\n| Auth | None (public endpoint) |\n| Content-Type | `application/json` |\n\n**Purpose:** Alternative authentication endpoint. Returns an access token upon successful login.\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `200 OK` with authentication credentials.\n\n---\n\n## 2\\. User Management Module\n\n### POST `/users/add` — Create User\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | POST |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/users/add` |\n| Auth | Bearer Token (`{{accessToken}}`) |\n| Content-Type | `application/json` |\n\n**Request Body:**\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"firstName\": \"John\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n  \"age\": 30,\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Purpose:** Creates a new user record in the system.\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `201 Created` with the newly created user object including an assigned `id`.\n\n---\n\n### GET `/users/5` — GET User\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | GET |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/users/5` |\n| Auth | Bearer Token (`{{accessToken}}`) |\n\n**Purpose:** Retrieves the details of a specific user by their ID (id=5).\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `200 OK` with the user object containing `id`, `firstName`, `lastName`, `age`, and `email`.\n\n---\n\n### PUT `/users/1` — Update User (PUT id=1)\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | PUT |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/users/1` |\n| Auth | Bearer Token (`{{accessToken}}`) |\n| Content-Type | `application/json` |\n\n**Request Body:**\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"firstName\": \"Janet\",\n  \"age\": 31\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Purpose:** Updates specific fields of an existing user (id=1).\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `200 OK` with the updated user object reflecting the new values.\n\n---\n\n### DELETE `/users/5` — Delete User (id=1)\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | DELETE |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/users/5` |\n| Auth | Bearer Token (`{{accessToken}}`) |\n\n**Purpose:** Deletes a user record from the system by ID.\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `200 OK` with a confirmation that the user has been deleted.\n\n---\n\n### GET `/users/999999` — Fetch Invalid User (id=999999)\n\n| Field | Details |\n| --- | --- |\n| Method | GET |\n| URL | `{{baseUrl}}/users/999999` |\n| Auth | Bearer Token (`{{accessToken}}`) |\n\n**Purpose:** Negative test case — attempts to fetch a user with a non-existent ID to validate proper error handling.\n\n**Expected Outcome:** `404 Not Found` with an appropriate error message.\n\n---\n\n## 3\\. Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `{{baseUrl}}` | Base URL of the API under test |\n| `{{accessToken}}` | JWT token obtained after successful login |\n| `{{userId}}` | Dynamic user ID set during test execution |\n| `{{latencyWarning}}` | Threshold (ms) for response time assertions |\n\n---\n\n## 4\\. Test Coverage Summary\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Test Type | Status |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `/user/login` | POST | Auth / Positive | ✅ |\n| `/auth/login` | POST | Auth / Positive | ✅ |\n| `/users/add` | POST | CRUD / Positive | ✅ |\n| `/users/5` | GET | CRUD / Positive | ✅ |\n| `/users/1` | PUT | CRUD / Positive | ✅ |\n| `/users/5` | DELETE | CRUD / Positive | ✅ |\n| `/users/999999` | GET | Negative / Error | ✅ |\n\n---\n\n## 5\\. Notes\n\n- All requests use `{{baseUrl}}` which is configured in the **Assessment - Env** environment.\n    \n- The `{{accessToken}}` variable should be set automatically via a post-response script on the Login request.\n    \n- The **Reports** folder serves as the documentation and reporting hub for this collection.\n    \n- Generated: 2026-03-26"
    }
  ]
